:$(2): \quad \paren {\dfrac a b}^2 \in \Q$
where $\Q$ denotes the set of rational numbers.


{{EuclidPropStatement|book=X|prop=73|body=If from a rational straight line there be subtracted a rational straight line commensurable with the whole in square only, the remainder is irrational; and let it be called an '''''apotome'''''.}}





