It is a '''mistake''' to suggest that $a$ and $b$ may be ''any'' real numbers such that $\dfrac a b \notin \Q$ and $\paren {\dfrac a b}^2 \in \Q$.

For example, let $a = \pi \sqrt 2$ and $b = \pi$.

